When we have no more self, no more afflictions, that is the ultimate happiness.

27
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:53,500
I further summarize these four.

28
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:57,500
Samsara means our five aggregates.

29
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:00,500
Our body and mind.

30
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:05,500
We are suffering right now because we have the five aggregates.

31
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:08,500
Our form, which is our body.

32
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:15,500
Our feelings, perception, mental formation and consciousness.

33
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:17,500
The first one is our body.

34
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,300
The next four is our mind.

35
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:22,300
The next four is our mind.

36
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:25,300
So body and mind.

37
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:29,300
We are attached to our body and mind.

38
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:31,300
We think that is me.

39
00:02:31,300 --> 00:02:34,300
We have a perception of the self.

40
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:37,300
That is why we are in Samsara.

41
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:44,300
Buddha wants us to contemplate on the four mindfulness about the five aggregates.

42
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:48,300
Our body, our form is impure.

43
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:58,300
Every day trying to decorate this body and make it healthy and perfect or have sexual desires about other people's body.

44
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:06,300
If we can see how impure everyone's body is, you will love your body so much and we will get rid of the self.

45
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:08,300
Then our feelings.

46
00:03:08,300 --> 00:03:12,300
We have to contemplate that it is only suffering.

47
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:17,300
We think we can gain happiness when our worldly desires are fulfilled.

48
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:21,300
For example, we have great food.

49
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:23,300
