90
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:04,300
That's why we dislike others.

91
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:05,300
We are selfish.

92
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:09,300
We protect our body, protect this image

93
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:11,300
because we have a strong sense of self.

94
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:17,300
So we have to see that we have the wrong view of the self.

95
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:21,300
The second one is the one-sided view.

96
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:26,300
One-sided means either we believe in emptiness

97
00:06:26,300 --> 00:06:29,300
or we believe in existence.

98
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:32,300
Some people believe in emptiness,

99
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:37,300
which means when we die, it's like a candle that's blown out.

100
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:38,300
That's all.

101
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:41,300
That is people that dwell on emptiness.

102
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:45,300
Some people dwell on existence.

103
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:49,300
They believe human will be human next lifetime

104
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:51,300
and human next lifetime.

105
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:52,300
Forever you'll be human.

106
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:56,300
That is people that believe in existence.

107
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:59,300
But both of these views are incorrect.

108
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:02,300
They are only one-sided.

109
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:04,300
It's not the middle way.

110
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:09,300
The middle way is not emptiness or existence.

111
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:13,300
It's this balance of emptiness and existence.

112
